Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.70,0:41:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,our
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.70,0:41:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.96,0:41:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.96,0:41:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,will try to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.96,0:41:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,justify
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.28,0:41:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,our fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.28,0:41:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.28,0:41:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,will try
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.28,0:41:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to justify
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.28,0:41:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,our fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.28,0:41:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.28,0:42:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that's
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.28,0:42:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the most
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.28,0:42:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,important
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.28,0:42:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,thing to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.50,0:42:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,think
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.50,0:42:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,about.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.50,0:42:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.50,0:42:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,not
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.50,0:42:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,going
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.50,0:42:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.50,0:42:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,go
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.50,0:42:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,out
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.50,0:42:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.50,0:42:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,choice
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.50,0:42:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.50,0:42:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,way that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.50,0:42:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.50,0:42:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is not
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.50,0:42:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,going
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.50,0:42:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.50,0:42:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,on such
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.50,0:42:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And my free choice is made by a mind which is not fearful.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.54,0:42:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the not-fearfulness is why I'm alive today to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.64,0:42:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not being afraid that held back the rattlesnake from striking when he was really
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.90,0:42:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,only inches away.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.25,0:42:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the loss of the fear, the letting go of the fearfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.19,0:42:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And having been in very severe, you might say to the eyes of the usual observer, dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.35,0:42:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,situations, and experienced only joy and happiness and trust in those circumstances, and walked
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.57,0:43:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,through cutthroats who would have really attacked a person who was holding fear and did it with
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.53,0:43:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a happy, gleeful smile on the faces of everyone, I mean, they got off on it that a guy like
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.75,0:43:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,me would walk right through them, you know, with their guns and chains and knives.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.28,0:43:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Had I come from fear, they would have challenged that and danger would really have arisen.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.64,0:43:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was the letting go.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.84,0:43:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting go of the fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.40,0:43:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So when they saw there was no fear, there was nothing to bounce off.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.26,0:43:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting go of the worst scenario then is extremely beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.84,0:43:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As we do this, we'll get to an awareness that something has been setting up the fear within
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.00,0:43:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,us, that now we've lost our fear of fear, and when it arises, we just walk around with
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.64,0:43:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.64,0:43:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I've walked around with fear for two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.20,0:43:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I let fear run one time for two solid weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.88,0:43:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That trembling.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.02,0:43:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That electric feeling ran through the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.34,0:43:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I went about my business, just kept letting it run.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.10,0:43:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I just let it run.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.44,0:43:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So let it run.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.46,0:44:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You let it run when you realize it'll run out.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.88,0:44:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But as we do that, you may come across that there is another source underlying this fear
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.20,0:44:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to begin with, and we come up against guilt as the source of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.42,0:44:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We now begin to see the value of work that the world calls spiritual consciousness, whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.86,0:44:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,terminology.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.86,0:44:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to see the value of, for instance, techniques such as concentrating on the value
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.00,0:44:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.58,0:44:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We see forgiving our self and forgiving our human beings, and turning over any judgment
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.60,0:44:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.94,0:44:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to see, if not to God, to some higher power, some energy, fate, whatever you want
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.60,0:44:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.36,0:44:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We find that by letting go, condemning our self and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.18,0:44:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We find that by letting go, condemning our self and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.18,0:44:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That the unconscious guilt, that that builds up, then also begins to alleviate fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.48,0:45:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because fear, then, you see, is held in mind because we expect the return of our attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.14,0:45:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We expect revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.54,0:45:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We expect retaliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.95,0:45:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So every negative thought that we hold, every hostile thought that we hold about others,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.25,0:45:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,engenders our own fearfulness, because on the psychic plane, on the mental plane, on
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.19,0:45:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the plane which is invisible to the naked eye. It is though we are building up for ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.59,0:45:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is going to come back to ourself. And so we learn that fearfulness begins to
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.48,0:45:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,diminish as we let go our angriness, hostile, critical, our thoughts which condemn others
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.48,0:45:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that make them wrong. And we learn the value of letting go the thoughts that make other
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.80,0:45:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,people wrong. We begin to value them and love them for their beingness, for what they
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.40,0:45:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,are. We begin to see ourself as different. Therefore we begin to see others as different.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.14,0:46:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We become willing to forgive, willing to forget, willing to overlook. We begin to see that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.96,0:46:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,all the things that we have condemned in others are really expressions of their humanness.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.84,0:46:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What we have been condemning in ourself and what we have been condemning in everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.14,0:46:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,else is their humanness.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.04,0:46:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The innocence of the little child within them that believed everything it heard as
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.42,0:46:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it grew up. What do you suppose the political persuasion of a person is as they grew up
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.56,0:46:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as an innocent child? The consciousness of the child is innocent, is it not? It loves
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.86,0:46:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,its parents, it trusts its parents, it loves the mother. And therefore the innocence of
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.36,0:46:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the child is what gets programmed. It is the innocent child that believes everything that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.82,0:46:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it is told, that the teacher tells it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.86,0:46:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The political programming that comes in via television, via the political system of the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.60,0:47:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,country. I ask you, who bought that? Who bought what you believe? To the listener right
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.77,0:47:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,now, all the belief systems in your mind, who bought them? You know who bought them?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.71,0:47:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind of the innocent child within you. Because that innocent child's mind, the nature
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.23,0:47:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself, has not changed since you were born. That which is listening to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.04,0:47:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,me right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.60,0:47:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the innocent consciousness of the child. Listening, alertly, saying, should I believe
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.36,0:47:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,what he's saying? Should I take it within myself? The innocent child never dies. That
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.54,0:47:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,innocence is still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.33,0:47:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you begin to see that intrinsic innocence and you realize that all the things that you
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.45,0:47:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,ever learned that ended up wrong were bought out of that intrinsic not knowing the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.03,0:47:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and learning that which was not the truth. Therefore we're willing to let go of our condemnation
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.87,0:47:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.75,0:47:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We're beginning to own our own innocence and the innocence of others. Misfortunate, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.73,0:48:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Regretful that the misinformation came into the innocent mind. You might look at the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.88,0:48:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of as the hardware of the computer and its belief systems as the software. Can the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.92,0:48:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,five year old child in Russia think other than the political system that he hears in
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.52,0:48:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,his kindergarten from his fellow students, from those parents, from his friends, from
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.36,0:48:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,his parents, from his family, from his grandparents, you begin to see it's out of his not knowingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.20,0:48:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it's out of the innocence of his not knowingness, that he believes what he believes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.74,0:48:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We're willing to forgive others then and instead of condemning them, understand them. And out
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.32,0:48:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of this understanding then, develops a certain compassion. The compassionate person has no
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.74,0:48:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,fears. What is there to fear in a compassionate world? Inasmuch as we're the source of our
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.50,0:48:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,own experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.06,0:48:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Our compassion as we own it back within ourself, as we see our own innocence and the innocence of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.20,0:49:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,others, brings to us the experience of a compassionate and loving world. No longer do
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.25,0:49:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we walk around fearfully because we are not creating it ourselves anymore. We see that we
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.41,0:49:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,were the source of our fears. The world was never the source of our fear. We are the source of the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.37,0:49:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,fear. Having let go creating it, having let go propagating it through the endless guilt which
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.49,0:49:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,comes about and through the endless judgments which social conditioning has brought us into
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.13,0:49:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the habit of, having let go of this now the unconscious guilt diminishes. The letting go of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.18,0:49:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,unconscious guilt progresses outside of our awareness. When we decide instead of condemning
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.61,0:49:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that person, I'm going to try to understand him. Every time we do that, our own store of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.31,0:49:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,unconscious guilt goes down. As our store of unconscious guilt goes down, the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.91,0:49:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,existence of our own conscience goes down. The existence of our own conscience goes down.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.01,0:49:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The existence of our own conscience goes down. The existence of our own conscience goes down.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.03,0:49:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,expectation of retaliation goes down. You see, in the unconscious, it's an eye for an
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.75,0:50:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,eye, a tooth for a tooth. If you wish somebody would drop dead, what do you suppose its equal
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.14,0:50:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is in your unconscious mind? That you should drop dead. You don't think that your thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.88,0:50:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,about if only your so-and-so would drop dead has anything to do with your fears of a heart
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.90,0:50:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,attack? Of course they do. As you let go wishing other people would drop dead, you'll find
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.95,0:50:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,curiously enough that your fear and obsession that you're going to get a coronary, you might
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.15,0:50:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,get a coronary, and all the dietary nonsense that goes with that will diminish. Instead you're very
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.37,0:50:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,peaceful about the whole thing. When you go, you go. If you stay, you stay. Big deal. What you value
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.27,0:50:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is life and you no longer focus on the potential ending of that life. So you come into a different
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.09,0:50:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,experience of the experiencing of life. You come into a different feeling about who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.17,0:50:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,See, I am that in which this experiencing is going on. And like the ox herding pictures
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.86,0:51:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that we've referred to before, instead of being dragged about by the ox of fear against
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.00,0:51:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our will with bleeding knees and rumpled clothes, now we tie this ox to a tree. Now we've located
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.32,0:51:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the culprit, where he is, you see. Having let go our fear of him now, we've become the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.10,0:51:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,master. We get on top of the ox, the ox becomes tame. We are
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.76,0:51:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the master.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.00,0:51:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Master, we've identified now with that which we really are, no longer the victim, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.03,0:51:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Victim comes out of unconsciousness. It means being unaware of this game setup that's been
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.57,0:51:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,going on within our mind. Merely becoming aware of it means that you're already out
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.69,0:51:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of it. By the time you've heard this talk today, you've gotten up from being victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.40,0:51:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're already tying this ox to the tree. That's what we're doing today, is tying that
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.78,0:51:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,ox to the tree. And then, as you practice these techniques we've described, you'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.01,0:52:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting on top of the ox. When the fear comes along, you welcome it. You say, great, what
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.11,0:52:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,an opportunity to let go more of that. Because by now you're feeling the benefit. You're
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.93,0:52:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling the decrease of fear and fears that you've had your whole lifetime. Little do
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.85,0:52:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,people realize the extent of the fear that they're holding until it begins to disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.29,0:52:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it's mind-boggling. You say, I never realized that was such a fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.27,0:52:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a fearful human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.36,0:52:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps more easily understood by referring back to this map of consciousness, so that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.24,0:52:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we can see how the energy fields here relate to the way we experience the world. You see,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.18,0:52:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,mind is so powerful that the way it holds your experience literally determines your
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.24,0:52:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,experience. Fearfulness creates a certain view of the world, and it becomes a self-fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.77,0:52:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-fulfilling prophecy. In psychoanalysis, psychiatry, it's called the self-fulfilling
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.09,0:53:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,prophecy. And recent university research, as well as our own research in Sedona, shows
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.71,0:53:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that what you hold in mind tends to make it happen within what you think is the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.71,0:53:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of your own experience, then, becomes the external representation, actually, of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.17,0:53:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,what you have been holding in mind. So that your life, the world, is really a world of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.15,0:53:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,mirrors.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.09,0:53:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're actually seeing, what you're actually experiencing, is a projection of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.06,0:53:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,your own level of consciousness. This is hard to believe and hard to really fully grasp,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.04,0:53:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but to give us a glimpse at it, it's a whole field of study in itself. On this map of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.18,0:53:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,let's compare the level of consciousness with its emotion and our view of the world, and
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.60,0:53:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,how this would give us a view of God if we believed in such consciousness.
