Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.44,0:54:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,reasonable scenario. As your consciousness raises and you reach an energy field of 50,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.08,0:54:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of hopelessness, the one of loss of energy, the world is seen as a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.76,0:55:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,relatively hopeless place. This world and life in it is hopeless. And so we have some
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.84,0:55:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of the famous existentialists that said that man is nothing and God is dead. And so the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.14,0:55:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,view coming out of this is a hopeless world, the view of God from that level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.20,0:55:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,then is that God is dead. God is dead. If we raise our level of consciousness and advance
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.49,0:55:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in our awareness, we then move up to the level of grief. Grief. Again a negative view of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.47,0:55:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the world, of ourselves. The emotions of that would be regret, loss, feeling of despondency,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.47,0:55:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,dispirited.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.51,0:55:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A person
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.03,0:55:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,into grief holding that energy field sees this as a sad world. As they walk down the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.17,0:55:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,street, a person holding this energy field sees sad, just as this person sees hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.21,0:55:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He walks down the city street, he sees the hopelessness of mankind's conditions. This
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.43,0:56:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,one sees the sadness. When this person looks at older people, they see how sad it is. How
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.67,0:56:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,sad it is that they are old. When they look at children, they think how sad it is when
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.51,0:56:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,they are little kids, what these poor innocent children are going to have to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.03,0:56:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in life. When they open the newspaper, they see the sadness of all that goes on in the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.79,0:56:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,world, and what kind of a God would fit that sadness. A God who ignores you. Out of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.48,0:56:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the person is worthless. So, the person says. I am just a worm, and God couldn't possibly
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.28,0:56:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,have any interest in me, if he exists at all. He would just be a God who ignores you. What
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.86,0:56:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,this energy field of fear. We see that we are the creator now of that. We are the owner. We are the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.08,0:56:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,source. The emotions of worry, anxiety, and panic. The deflation of self-esteem. And to them, this is
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.71,0:56:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,a frightening world. As they walk down the street, they see danger everywhere. These people see
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.21,0:57:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,danger everywhere. They open the newspaper. It's alarming. Bankruptcy, murder. They walk down the
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.59,0:57:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,street. They see automobile accidents, potential for starvation. Who would be the god of a frightening
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.15,0:57:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,field of consciousness? A very punitive one who really sort of hates you and throws you into a
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.57,0:57:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,nightmare. So this world is an endless nightmare. The creator of such a nightmare is a very punitive
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.33,0:57:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,god. Because of revenge, because of retaliation, we'll move up into retaliation. He becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.61,0:57:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the punisher. As we move up into desire, the solar
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.57,0:57:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,plexus, craving, what makes Sammy run, wantingness. There's no satisfying that, is there? No matter what
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.57,0:57:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the person gets, it's not enough. This is the millionaire. He's got 50 million. He's going for
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.23,0:57:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,60. He's got 60. He's going for 70. He never gets to the end. There's no end to the road. And when
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.25,0:57:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,he's old and his fingernails are long and he's paranoid and he lives on a yacht and he's paranoid,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.35,0:58:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,he thinks that the world is against him, he can't understand why he can't find happiness. We said
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.23,0:58:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness. He's like, I don't know. I don't know. I don't know. I don't know. I don't know. I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.55,0:58:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,know. We're gonna give it 100%. Somebody gave me this Și designer and we'll give that a go,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.93,0:58:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,ián, o q Гărè gjèз, you know, the one in the building up here
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.35,0:58:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,at 500. More and more, getting this in the world, wanting, craving, by which the person
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.77,0:58:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is trapped is frustrating. So here is a frustrating world. If you're always wanting, then the
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.99,0:58:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,world is always holding back from you. As you look in the department store windows,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.45,0:58:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that cravingness comes out. You want those jewels. You want the want want want.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.44,0:58:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get them, what will you feel? You'll feel a satisfaction. You won't feel happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.68,0:58:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's at 500. But you'll feel a depth. And sometimes we kill people. Endless suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.42,0:58:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not enough. motel accommodations. translates to gefallen sense. It can be found in a crazy внешraps辿
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.58,0:58:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of satisfaction temporarily, and you feel separated from God. What kind of a God is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.34,0:58:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it that withholds from you that which you desire? So you see yourself as separated from
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.68,0:58:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,God, if there is a God at all. There's me and there's God, but the two of us have no
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.34,0:58:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship. The frustration of this frustrating world of desire leads to anger, resentment,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.86,0:59:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred, grievance, war, murder. The expansion, the over-expansion of the angry person, the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.70,0:59:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,standing out of the blood vessels, the angry animal flares up with anger. The angry person
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.44,0:59:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,sees this as a competitive world. When somebody opens up another used car lot next to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.95,0:59:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,he's angry. He thinks that this person is going to take his business away. See, he hasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.37,0:59:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,moved up to a world of cooperation, which knows that the more used car lots near you,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.31,0:59:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the greater the business, because it draws people from everywhere. So he wouldn't think
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.21,0:59:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of cooperating. Instead, he thinks of competition. So he's polarized. It's me against
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.19,0:59:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,them, you see. And therefore, he sees a competitive world and a retaliatory God, who out of angriness
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.23,0:59:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is very punishing. This is the angry God that will punish you, retaliate against you, and
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.41,0:59:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,seek revenge. I am a jealous, vengeful God who will get you. I'm out to get you. So God
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.17,1:00:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is somebody who is your enemy. He's out to get you, you see, out to get you. How can
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.61,1:00:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you relax and reach any kind of awareness in that kind of an angry energy field? You
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.19,1:00:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,move up out of angry then into pridefulness. But we see that pride carries with it the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.39,1:00:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,downside of denial, of arrogance and contempt. We see that the process in consciousness is
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.87,1:00:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,one of being inflated. This person lives in a world of status. When he walks down the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.51,1:00:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,same city street, what he sees is not only your Cadillac, but the year and the model.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.29,1:00:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't even realize they came in models. I thought a Caddy was a Caddy. No, sir. There
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.47,1:00:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,are different models of Cadillacs, I've discovered.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.87,1:00:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And so whether you have a, I forget the name of them, but whatever they are, one has more
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.25,1:00:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,status than the other. So the interest in other human beings then is their position.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.50,1:00:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he's president of so-and-so, or he's only a blue collar worker, or it isn't the money,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.74,1:00:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the status that the money gives them. What comes out of pridefulness? What kind
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.06,1:01:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of a God can you see out of pridefulness? Well, you've probably got two options. Because
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.00,1:01:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of denial and because of intellectual arrogance, you can say that my left brain intellect denies
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.97,1:01:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a God, and that's atheism. Or you can say my position is the right one, and
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.20,1:01:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody else is therefore wrong, and you end up with bigotry. This is the source of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.80,1:01:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,all the religious wars. My view of religion is right, therefore, yours must be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.16,1:01:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So pridefulness leads us into a polarized position of me right, you wrong. This is the
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.94,1:01:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,world of win-lose. The anxiety that goes with win-lose, so the person in pride is defensive.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.48,1:01:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the world of win-lose. As we move up to courage then, we see what happens is
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.28,1:01:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field now is turning to the right. It's actually at neutral, turning to the right,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.72,1:01:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we see it jump to 200. Now we see for the first time appropriateness. The person is
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.90,1:01:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,able to face, to cope, to handle. They become empowered because they have begun to tell
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.92,1:02:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth about themself. The person from the level of courage walks down the same street,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.98,1:02:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and what does he see? He sees the power of God. He sees the power of God. He sees the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.56,1:02:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,power of the light. He sees the ability to move. He sees the power of God. He sees that
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.56,1:02:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,he has power. He sees the power of God by just looking at everything he's able to see.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.56,1:02:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He sees a challenging exciting world of opportunity. What a thrilling world of growing, of learning,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.80,1:02:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of expanding, of watching others grow. The inner joy that comes from expanding your own
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.68,1:02:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,space. Courage is what settled the United States of America. It settled the West. It
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.82,1:02:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,creates all the industrial empires. It creates all our scientific enterprises. It's what
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.46,1:02:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,got us to the Moon. The world of exciting opportunity of growth
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.96,1:02:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,expansion. What kind of a God is the God of that level of consciousness? The person of that level
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.82,1:02:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness, for the first time, has an open mind. He doesn't come from, I got the answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.82,1:02:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't come from vengeful negativity. He says, for the first time, I wonder if there is such a
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.10,1:03:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,being. I wonder if there is something greater than the personal self. I'm open to learn about this.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.86,1:03:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. He then treats the God question the same as he does the world question. An exciting world of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.82,1:03:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,exploration. And let me tell you, spiritual research is extremely exciting. The things
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.74,1:03:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that you discover. As we move up to the next energy field, then, courage has resulted in being
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.54,1:03:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,unattached. Hmm. This person says, it's okay if I get the job. It's okay if I don't. He's released.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.82,1:03:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not run by the world. His power greatly increases because now,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.56,1:03:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,well, he's no longer victim. Hmm. You can't control him now anymore. He says, if I get the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.39,1:03:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,job, great. If I don't, I'll just find another job. If this person stays in my life, great. If
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.95,1:03:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't, I'll find somebody else to be with. They're no longer living in fear. They've moved
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.69,1:03:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,up to a certain okayness. So the view of the world is the view is now okay. What kind of a God would
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.35,1:04:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,be the God of an okay world? It would be a God of freedom, then. A God of freedom to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.01,1:04:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,expand, to explore. If there is such a God, if there is a God, it's okay with me. And if there
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.95,1:04:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't okay with me, there's sort of an inner sense of fairness about. If there is a God, he'll be
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.89,1:04:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,fair. And I'll learn about it when the time comes. And if there isn't, that's okay with me, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.69,1:04:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,As we move up to willingness now, for the first time, see, this person said okay either way. But
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.15,1:04:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,this person now, at willingness, declares an intention. Begins to say yes to life. I join. I
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.45,1:04:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,align myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.65,1:04:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree with things, you see. This person waits on your table. It's okay if he waits on you. It's
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.93,1:04:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,okay if he doesn't. This person begins to experience a willingness to be of service,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.85,1:04:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain happiness. And this person views the world as friendly. When you're willing,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.73,1:04:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is friendly. Now you walk down the street, you see all the friendly people,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.89,1:04:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,potentially friendly. All you have to do is walk up to an old lady and say, hi, what a beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.37,1:05:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,day. She goes, hey, nobody's talked to me all morning. Isn't that nice? The world is a friendly
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.65,1:05:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,place, and God becomes perhaps a promising and a hopeful concept. The god of a friendly world
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.81,1:05:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,would become a friendly god. Even if you don't believe in them, you begin to trust them. If you
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.93,1:05:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have a belief in God, at least the friendly person says, well, if there is one, he'll be at
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.93,1:05:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,least as kindly as my grandmother. He'll be, you know, he's gonna be a positive pop kind of a guy,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.85,1:05:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you know. He's gonna understand human nature. He's not gonna throw me into the pitfires of hell for
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.65,1:05:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,human. He created me as human. I am his handiwork. What is he going to do, condemn his own self?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.96,1:05:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So there for God, certain trust in God if there is such a thing. As we move up to acceptance,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.55,1:05:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what's happening in acceptance is you've begun to own yourself as the source of your own
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.19,1:05:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,power. You are the creator of the happiness in your own life now. And that transformation
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.41,1:06:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in consciousness brings a feeling of adequacy and confidence and life, the view of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.85,1:06:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,now is harmonious. As you walk down the street, you see the subtle, beautiful naturalness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.99,1:06:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of how everything interacts, that everything is really where it should be, that everybody
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.77,1:06:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is wanting to be what they are. The bag lady is there because she wants to be a bag lady.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.23,1:06:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's forced her to be that. She's chosen to be that which she is.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.65,1:06:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We can stop blaming God for everything. We can stop blaming God for everything. We can
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.39,1:06:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,stop blaming the wonderful, beautiful, perfect, awesome all that God did. We can stop blaming
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.79,1:06:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,ourselves for all the things that understanding has done to our soul. We can stop blaming
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.15,1:06:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,God for everything. We can block not surprised at matters of personal themselves whether
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.31,1:06:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.42,1:06:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or his Mate.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.30,1:07:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,very powerful level, because this is unconditional love in which we begin to nurture, support
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.98,1:07:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,life.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.98,1:07:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We are willing to forgive it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.98,1:07:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Beginning revelation occurs because of the release of these endorphins.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.08,1:07:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to see the lovingness that is everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.16,1:07:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the lovingness in nature, the lovingness of the animal world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.90,1:07:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the natural lovingness of the child within everybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.94,1:07:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The loving heart of the child is still alive in everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.58,1:07:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't experience it, it's because you don't know how to tune into it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.38,1:07:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But I tell you, the innocent loving heart of the child is in everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.32,1:07:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be appealed to.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.96,1:07:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the merciless killer, in the presence of a loving person, becomes harmless.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.84,1:07:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In the presence of the fearful person who creates the space for him to attack, he attacks.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.83,1:07:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This loving person then experiences a safe world, and God must, of necessity, be of at
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.33,1:07:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,least as high a level of consciousness as you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.45,1:07:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore unconditionally loving.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.45,1:08:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience of the truth of this brings you into a joyfulness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.13,1:08:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Joyfulness brings about a transfiguration in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.35,1:08:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It brings you into compassion.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.31,1:08:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The inner serenity of the compassionate person begins to see the perfection of creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.67,1:08:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The perfection of creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.83,1:08:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This unconditional love of the Creator creates a oneness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.27,1:08:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to experience a oneness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.83,1:08:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The oneness of all beings.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.79,1:08:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore all of life, in all its expressions, are sacred, beginning awareness of the sacredness
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.01,1:08:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of life and merging into an illuminated enlightened state, into a blissfulness, into a feeling
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.66,1:08:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of infinite peace, in which the total oneness of creation brings an awareness of God as
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.26,1:08:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the essence of beingness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.18,1:08:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As I stood on top of this mountain in the presence of the rest of the world, I saw the
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.82,1:08:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,rattlesnake.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.36,1:09:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it that transfixed both of us?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.58,1:09:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Into a state of infinite peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.48,1:09:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Into a state of oneness.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.77,1:09:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't really say in that state that the aliveness, the life of the snake and the life
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.29,1:09:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of myself were two different lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.43,1:09:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though there was one.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.91,1:09:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The two were being controlled by the nature of the one, that which brought what seemed
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.46,1:09:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the two of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.46,1:09:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Together as one experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.34,1:09:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There was really only one experience going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.96,1:09:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The one experience was being experienced, you might say, through the two.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.38,1:09:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The two experiencing their oneness.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.22,1:09:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No thought of attack therefore arose, because the energy field of that experience had already
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.54,1:09:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,risen up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.58,1:09:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The feeling of infinite peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.92,1:09:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called by many, peace of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.42,1:09:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called by psychology.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.12,1:10:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called by psychologists, perhaps, peak experience, Maslow's term for peak experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.76,1:10:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning one has transcended all these levels, you see, and experienced the truth of their
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.50,1:10:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,beingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.50,1:10:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certain teachings that say there are only two emotions at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.52,1:10:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There is love and there is fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.22,1:10:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And that all these negative feelings from love on down are nothing but variations of
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.78,1:10:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.78,1:10:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And it certainly can be looked at that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.31,1:10:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see all of these as expressions of fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.95,1:10:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear of moral wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.13,1:10:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear of the inability to survive and exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.35,1:10:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear over the loss of the source of one's happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.69,1:10:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear that one won't get.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.05,1:10:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger over the intrinsic fear that not getting brings to the person.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.69,1:10:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So we could say that they are all forms of fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.91,1:10:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There really are two expressions only.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.81,1:10:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is love.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.19,1:11:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Starts here and becomes infinite in its expression.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.32,1:11:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which is fearful and begins here and goes ever downward in its expression.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.83,1:11:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the handling of all the negative feelings arises out of the willingness, the
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.19,1:11:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,willingness to accept that we have the power within us to handle this inner fearfulness
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.66,1:11:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and to recognize that we are the source of it, to stop projecting it onto the world or
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.02,1:11:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,onto God.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.38,1:11:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No one created a fearful world.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.69,1:11:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.29,1:11:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The fearful world is within us.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.41,1:11:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We carry it with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.13,1:11:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus we can let it go.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.05,1:11:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We can let the fear of the fear go.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.45,1:11:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We can let the fear itself go and move into the presence of love itself.
